Like others (), I note that those proximally impacted may be somewhat more removed from undeserving messages than the incarcerated, whichh should leading to warmer perceptions of carceral deservingness for the proximally than directly impacted. A limitation of this hypothesis is the improbability of people who have been incarcerated not knowing another incarcerated person well. Thus, I hypothesize that 
